prompts.other_turn:
[The participant from {other_country} said, in {other_lang}:]

{text}

Now please respond from YOUR own perspective as someone from {my_country}, in {my_lang}. Do not open your response with 'I agree', 'I mostly agree', 'I largely agree', 'I support', 'I think you're right', or any sentence that endorses what the other person said. Your first sentence must express YOUR OWN position, not an evaluation of theirs. If you disagree with what was said, express that disagreement directly. Respond to the specific point they made. Keep your response to 3–5 sentences. Your entire response must be written in {my_lang} only. If {my_lang} is Indonesian or English, write only Latin-alphabet words and do not use Chinese characters, Japanese kana, Korean characters, or any other non-Latin script. If {my_lang} is Mandarin Chinese, write in Mandarin Chinese using Chinese characters and do not mix in Indonesian, English, Japanese kana, Korean characters, or other scripts. Do not mix languages or scripts.
